gomodel:SYNGO_4030  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: Immunofluorescence micrograph of SGII, Aβ, and DβH in the prefrontal cortex. SGII (red), Aβ (blue), and DβH(green) were labelled separately and marked by arrowheads. Magenta indicates co-localization between Aβ with canonical DCV marker SgII, and are marked by a thick arrow.\n\nFigure 3: Immunoperoxidase-DβH and dual immunogold-silver labelling (large and small gold-silver particles, for Aβ and SGII, respectively) were localized in the same tissue section. Gold-silver labelling for Aβ and SGII were readily distinguishable from each other and were localized to the appropriate cellular structures. Aβ (marked by arrowheads) was identified by large-sized gold-silver particles (>50 nm cross-sectional diameter; average 65nm) while SGII was labelled (marked by arrows) using small-sized gold-silver particles (<40 nm cross-sectional diameter; average 31 nm).\n\nNote: The paper does not comment on specificity and cross-reactivity of Aβ or SGII antibodies.. Experimental description: The paper does not mention any details on the species used, just mentions that the micrography results were performed on the infralimbic medial prefrontal cortex of naïve rats." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4030" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

